 :root: n. [Unix] 1. The {superuser} account (with user name `root') that
ignores permission bits, user number 0 on a Unix system. The term {avatar} is
also used. 2. The top node of the system directory structure (home directory
of the root user). 3. By extension, the privileged system-maintenance login
on any OS. see {root mode}, {go root}, see also {wheel}.